"user":{"login":"The-Judge","id":904987,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjkwNDk4Nw==","avatar_url":"https://avatars1.githubusercontent.com/u/904987?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/The-Judge","html_url":"https://github.com/The-Judge","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/The-Judge/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/The-Judge/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/The-Judge/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/The-Judge/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/The-Judge/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/The-Judge/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/The-Judge/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/The-Judge/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/The-Judge/received_events","type":"User","site_admin":false},"created_at":"2020-07-21T12:24:15Z","updated_at":"2020-07-21T12:24:15Z","author_association":"NONE","body":"Hi @willmcgugan ;\r\n\r\nexactly, when it comes to the column layout.\r\nIf something like that could be implemented, plus the possibility to define different colors, font style (bold, blue, ...) to it, that would be a 100% match for this request.\r\n\r\nBR","performed_via_github_app":null},{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/willmcgugan/rich/issues/comments/661831456","html_url":"https://github.com/willmcgugan/rich/issues/164#issuecomment-661831456","issue_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/willmcgugan/rich/issues/164","id":661831456,"node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDY2MTgzMTQ1Ng==","user":{"login":"willmcgugan","id":554369,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjU1NDM2OQ==","avatar_url":"https://avatars3.githubusercontent.com/u/554369?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/willmcgugan","html_url":"https://github.com/willmcgugan","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/willmcgugan/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/willmcgugan/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/willmcgugan/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/willmcgugan/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/willmcgugan/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/willmcgugan/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/willmcgugan/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/willmcgugan/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/willmcgugan/received_events","type":"User","site_admin":false},"created_at":"2020-07-21T12:39:07Z","updated_at":"2020-07-21T12:39:07Z","author_association":"OWNER","body":"This is something I've been thinking about for a while. It's tricky to implement, but would be a nice feature. I'm hoping to get sponsorship for enhancements such as these. I'll keep this ticket open as a reminder. ","performed_via_github_app":null},{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/willmcgugan/rich/issues/comments/668086945","html_url":"https://github.com/willmcgugan/rich/issues/164#issuecomment-668086945","issue_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/willmcgugan/rich/issues/164","id":668086945,"node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDY2ODA4Njk0NQ==","user":{"login":"elicoten","id":12326933,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjEyMzI2OTMz","avatar_url":"https://avatars1.githubusercontent.com/u/12326933?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/elicoten","html_url":"https://github.com/elicoten","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/elicoten/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/elicoten/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/elicoten/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/elicoten/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/elicoten/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/elicoten/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/elicoten/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/elicoten/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/elicoten/received_events","type":"User","site_admin":false},"created_at":"2020-08-03T15:28:58Z","updated_at":"2020-08-03T15:29:33Z","author_association":"NONE","body":"I think in this case it's actually the equivalent of the html `colspan` attribute.\r\n\r\n`rowspan` is where a single cell covers multiple rows (i.e. the content extends into space where the cells **above/below** would be) as shown in the [w3schools example](https://www.w3schools.com/tags/tryit.asp?filename=tryhtml_td_rowspan).\r\n\r\nWhilst rowspan may also be a useful addition, I'm also here in search of a feature that enables an individual cell to expand across multiple columns - i.e. it extends horizontally, in the way shown in the image in https://github.com/willmcgugan/rich/issues/164#issuecomment-661731962.","performed_via_github_app":null},{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/willmcgugan/rich/issues/comments/672293842","html_url":"https://github.com/willmcgugan/rich/issues/164#issuecomment-672293842","issue_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/willmcgugan/rich/issues/164","id":672293842,"node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDY3MjI5Mzg0Mg==","user":{"login":"ericsaintetienne","id":14312824,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjE0MzEyODI0","avatar_url":"https://avatars0.githubusercontent.com/u/14312824?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/ericsaintetienne","html_url":"https://github.com/ericsaintetienne","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/ericsaintetienne/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/ericsaintetienne/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/ericsaintetienne/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/ericsaintetienne/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/ericsaintetienne/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/ericsaintetienne/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/ericsaintetienne/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/ericsaintetienne/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/ericsaintetienne/received_events","type":"User","site_admin":false},"created_at":"2020-08-11T21:41:47Z","updated_at":"2020-08-11T21:44:35Z","author_association":"NONE","body":"Other table libraries like dashtables support `rowspan` and `colspan` semantics. I'd like to see this coming to `rich` as well.\r\nThis is how it's done using dashtables:\r\n```\r\nfrom dashtable import data2rst\r\n\r\ntable = [\r\n        [\"Header 1\", \"Header 2\", \"Header3\", \"Header 4\"],\r\n        [\"row 1\", \"column 2\", \"column 3\", \"column 4\"],\r\n        [\"row 2\", \"Cells span columns.\", \"\", \"\"],\r\n        [\"row 3\", \"Cells\\nspan rows.\", \"- Cells\\n- contain\\n- blocks\", \"\"],\r\n        [\"row 4\", \"\", \"\", \"\"]\r\n    ]\r\n\r\n# [Row, Column] pairs of merged cells -- zero-based indexing\r\nspan0 = [[2, 1], [2, 2], [2, 3]]\r\nspan1 = [[3, 1], [4, 1]]\r\nspan2 = [[3, 2], [3, 3], [4, 2], [4, 3]]\r\n\r\nmy_spans = [span0, span1, span2]\r\n\r\nprint(data2rst(table, spans=my_spans, use_headers=True))\r\n```\r\nWhich outputs the following:\r\n```\r\n+----------+------------+----------+----------+\r\n| Header 1 | Header 2   | Header3  | Header 4 |\r\n+==========+============+==========+==========+\r\n| row 1    | column 2   | column 3 | column 4 |\r\n+----------+------------+----------+----------+\r\n| row 2    | Cells span columns.              |\r\n+----------+------------+---------------------+\r\n| row 3    | Cells      | - Cells             |\r\n+----------+ span rows. | - contain           |\r\n| row 4    |            | - blocks            |\r\n+----------+------------+---------------------+\r\n```","performed_via_github_app":null},{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/willmcgugan/rich/issues/comments/735880045","html_url":"https://github.com/willmcgugan/rich/issues/164#issuecomment-735880045","issue_url":"htt